The Professional Golfers Association of Nigeria (PGAN) will admit young women aspiring to become professionals into the Qualifying School (QS) in the 2019/2020 session. In this regard, the School is said to have redesigned its contents and focus in line with international best practices. This development, Samson Lawal, the PGAN Director said would enable graduants of the school to compete favorably with others from other climes. “We want our products to be able to compete with other professionals, not only in playing, but also in other aspects of the game. “This has been our dream and it has become a reality. The Ladies Golf Association of Nigeria (LGAN) has been enthusiastic about it,” Lawal said. Jide Bolaji, Secreatry general of the association corroborating the Director affirmed, “The Qualifying School is aimed at producing professionals that will identify and utilise modern technology in teaching golf. “They are also to be trained in the areas of golf course designs and maintenance as well as training of highly innovative and proactive professionals that will excel in any situation.” The Qualifying School which runs for a calendar year will commence from January 2019 to January 2020 with classroom and course work to test the mental and practical ability of the students. Ekanem Ekwueme, LGAN President had earlier said, “LGAN will partner with the PGA of Nigeria to improve golf in the country, particularly for the younger women that are interested in becoming professionals SHOCKING STORY!!! After 9 Years Of Suffering From Weak Erection & Premature Ejaculation, 43 Year Old Man Finally Discovers The Solution That Mysteriously Jerk His Dead Manhood Back To Life, Increased His "Rod" Size, And Now Last 32 Minutes In Bed. Click HERE! 